<headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued July 28 at 3:33PM EDT until July 28 at 11:00PM EDT by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM EDT THIS
EVENING...
* WHAT...High wave action, strong currents, and dangerous swimming
conditions expected. Piers will be heavily swamped by waves.
Waves of 2 to 4 feet will subside 1 to 3 feet overnight.
* WHERE...Berrien county.
* WHEN...Until 11 PM EDT this evening.
* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.</description>
<instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers.</instruction>
